        <briefdescription>
<para>Points to the first memory address after the last byte of the dictionary Points to the next <ref refid="struct_tuple" kindref="compound">Tuple</ref> in the dictionary. Given the end of the Dictionary has not yet been reached: when writing, the next key/value pair will be written at the cursor. When reading, the next call to <ref refid="group___dictionary_1ga0494e17cb2cb325f10d7c3172ecd676b" kindref="member">dict_read_next()</ref> will return the cursor. </para>
