    <briefdescription>
<para>An iterator can be used to iterate over the key/value tuples in an existing dictionary, using <ref refid="group___dictionary_1ga0d5d65d21509a42a3113f8b09768d8c5" kindref="member">dict_read_begin_from_buffer()</ref>, <ref refid="group___dictionary_1gac1443377d1e746e315fc943016885cf2" kindref="member">dict_read_first()</ref> and <ref refid="group___dictionary_1ga0494e17cb2cb325f10d7c3172ecd676b" kindref="member">dict_read_next()</ref>. An iterator can also be used to append key/value tuples to a dictionary, for example using <ref refid="group___dictionary_1ga30091feef740732d5d6bc3cf2312642a" kindref="member">dict_write_data()</ref> or <ref refid="group___dictionary_1ga015dfe89d0ee2f8b4e16ddda21bcf556" kindref="member">dict_write_cstring()</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
